y: none;"><g><path stroke="url(#__lottie_element_424)" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="miter" fill-opacity="0" stroke-miterlimit="4"></path></g></g><g style="display: none;"><g><path stroke="url(#__lottie_element_420)" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="miter" fill-opacity="0" stroke-miterlimit="4"></path></g></g><g style="display: none;"><g><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="miter" fill-opacity="0" stroke-miterlimit="4"></path></g></g><g style="display: none;"><g><path stroke="url(#__lottie_element_413)" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="miter" fill-opacity="0" stroke-miterlimit="4"></path></g></g></g></svg></div></div></bard-avatar><!----><!----></div><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c1421881827="" class="response-container-content ng-tns-c1421881827-43"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c4196027943="" class="response-content ng-tns-c1421881827-43"><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c4196027943="" class="thoughts-container ng-star-inserted"><!----></div><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><h2 _ngcontent-ng-c4196027943="" class="cdk-visually-hidden ng-star-inserted"> Gemini said </h2><!----><!----><structured-content-container _ngcontent-ng-c4196027943="" class="model-response-text processing-state-visible ng-star-inserted" _nghost-ng-c645682495="" style="height: auto;"><div _ngcontent-ng-c645682495="" class="container"><message-content _ngcontent-ng-c645682495="" _nghost-ng-c2062420164="" id="message-content-id-r_d976163207de423c" class="ng-star-inserted"><div _ngcontent-ng-c2062420164="" inline-copy-host="" class="markdown markdown-main-panel tutor-markdown-rendering stronger enable-updated-hr-color" style="--animation-duration: 400ms; --fade-animation-function: linear;" id="model-response-message-contentr_d976163207de423c" aria-live="polite" aria-busy="false" dir="ltr"><p data-path-to-node="0">You can certainly open Gemini in a new tab, but <b data-path-to-node="0" data-index-in-node="48">Google doesn't currently support passing a "pre-filled" text prompt via a URL parameter</b> (like some other services do with <code data-path-to-node="0" data-index-in-node="170">?q=your+text</code>).</p><p data-path-to-node="1">If you try to add a query to the end of the URL, it will generally just land you on the standard, empty home screen.</p><hr data-path-to-node="2"><h3 data-path-to-node="3">Your Best Options</h3><p data-path-to-node="4">Since you can't "inject" the text via the URL, here are the most efficient ways to handle this:</p><ul data-path-to-node="5"><li><p data-path-to-node="5,0,0"><b data-path-to-node="5,0,0" data-index-in-node="0">The Classic Copy-Paste:</b> It's low-tech, but it\'92s the most reliable. Open the tab with <code data-path-to-node="5,0,0" data-index-in-node="85">Ctrl/Cmd + T</code>, type <code data-path-to-node="5,0,0" data-index-in-node="104">gemini.google.com</code>, and paste your text.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="5,1,0"><b data-path-to-node="5,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">The "gemini" Shortcut (Chrome/Edge):</b> In your browser's address bar, type <b data-path-to-node="5,1,0" data-index-in-node="73">"gemini"</b> and hit <b data-path-to-node="5,1,0" data-index-in-node="90">Tab</b> or <b data-path-to-node="5,1,0" data-index-in-node="97">Space</b>. You can then type your request directly into the address bar; hitting <b data-path-to-node="5,1,0" data-index-in-node="174">Enter</b> will open a new tab with that prompt already processing.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node="5,2,0"><b data-path-to-node="5,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">Gemini Extension (Chrome):</b> If you use the Gemini Chrome extension, you can highlight text on any webpage, right-click, and select "Send to Gemini."</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node="6">For Developers</h3><p data-path-to-node="7">If you were looking to do this programmatically (e.g., via a script or an app), you would typically use the <b data-path-to-node="7" data-index-in-node="108">Google AI SDK</b> or the <b data-path-to-node="7" data-index-in-node="129">Vertex AI API</b> rather than trying to automate the browser interface. This allows you to send text and receive responses directly in your own code using:</p><div data-path-to-node="8"><div class="math-block" data-math="L_\{prompt\} \\rightarrow \\text\{Gemini API\} \\rightarrow R_\{response\}"><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.9694em; vertical-align: -0.2861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">L</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2806em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: 0em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">ro</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">m</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">pt</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">\uc0\u8203 </span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">\u8594 </span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Gemini&nbsp;API</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">\u8594 </span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.9694em; vertical-align: -0.2861em;"></span><span class="mord"><span style="margin-right: 0.0077em;" class="mord mathnormal">R</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.1514em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.55em; margin-left: -0.0077em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">res</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">p</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">n</span><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">se</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">\u8203 </span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.2861em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div><p data-path-to-node="9">Would you like me to show you how to set up a basic Python script to send text to Gemini via the API?</p></div></message-content><!----></div></structured-content-container><!----><!----><div _ngcontent-ng-c4196027943="" class="response-footer gap complete"><!----><!----><!----><sources-list _ngcontent-ng-c4196027943="" class="sources-list ng-star-inserted"><!----></sources-list><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></div></div><!----><sensitive-memories-banner _ngcontent-ng-c4196027943="" _nghost-ng-c1340904695="" class="ng-star-inserted" style=""><!----></sensitive-memories-banner><!----><!----><!----></div></div><div _ngcontent-ng-c1421881827="" class="response-container-footer ng-tns-c1421881827-43 ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----><message-actions _ngcontent-ng-c4196027943="" footer="" _nghost-ng-c4001672242="" class="ng-tns-c4001672242-45 ng-star-inserted" style=""><div _ngcontent-ng-c4001672242="" class="actions-container-v2 ng-tns-c4001672242-45"><div _ngcontent-ng-c4001672242="" class="buttons-container-v2 ng-tns-c4001672242-45 ng-star-inserted"><!----><thumb-up-button _ngcontent-ng-c4001672242="" _nghost-ng-c1157015512="" c